 * Each built-in theme declares a `variant` ("light" | "dark") so the web app
 * can derive the correct `.dark` class toggle from the selected theme.
 *
 * Color values use raw CSS color syntax (oklch / hex / etc.) so they can be
 * applied as inline style overrides on the document root.  The two "default"
 * themes (t3-dark, t3-light) intentionally mirror the stylesheet values in
 * `apps/web/src/index.css` — selecting them clears any inline overrides and
 * lets the compiled CSS take effect.
